# Coding Conventions

## Python
- Use `services/db.py` for all DB connections — never hardcode credentials
- All config via `.env` (python-dotenv), accessed with `os.getenv()`
- SAP column indices defined as `SAP_COL_*` constants at module level
- Output column names must match `OUTPUT_COLUMNS` list exactly (109 columns, A–DE)
- Use `parse_sap_number()` for any numeric SAP field (handles trailing minus, whitespace)
- Comments on output_df assignments should include Excel column letter: `# (BH) description`

## Frontend
- Single-page app in `templates/index.html` — vanilla JS, no framework
- API calls use `fetch()` with `FormData`
- Toast notifications for user feedback
- All styling inline in `<style>` block (no external CSS files)

## Docker
- Web and DB communicate via Docker internal network (service name `db`)
- MySQL port is `expose` only (not bound to host)
- `.env` file uses `DB_HOST=db` for Docker, change to `localhost` for local dev

## Adding New Output Columns
1. Add to `OUTPUT_COLUMNS` list with correct position and comment
2. Add SAP column constant if reading from SAP report
3. Add logic in the build section with `# (XX) Column Name:` comment
4. If column participates in subtotal/promotion rows, update `sum_cols`, `copy_cols`, or row builders
